# Web UI language (English only)

All strings shown to end users in the web client must be **English**, including:

- Button labels, headings, helper text, empty states
- `placeholder`, `title`, `aria-label`, `alt`
- Select/menu options, badges, tooltips
- Inline user-facing errors and toasts (`toast()`, Sonner, etc.)

## Allowed exceptions

- **Identifiers** in code (variable names, routes) — follow normal code style
- **Proper nouns** (product names, OEM terms, Knox, PCAN, etc.)
- **Formatted data** (numbers, dates via `Intl` with user locale) — the **pattern** is localized; surrounding labels stay English unless you add real i18n
- **Quoted third-party / user content** shown verbatim

## Do not

- Add German (or other non-English) UI copy for convenience during implementation; use English from the start
- Mix languages in the same surface (e.g. English title + German tooltip)

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<button title="Verbindung prüfen">Connect</button>

// ✅ GOOD
<button title="Check connection">Connect</button>
```

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<span>Zykluszeit seit letztem Frame</span>

// ✅ GOOD
<span>Time since previous frame with same ID</span>
```
